Note_en: (3) An increment of zero means that the statistical processing is the result of a continuous (or near-continuous) process, not the processing of a number of discrete samples. Examples of such continuous processes are the temperatures measured by analogue maximum and minimum thermometers or thermographs, and the rainfall measured by raingauge.
